    • Method Detail

      • getBodyLength

        Any getBodyLength()
        Gets the number of bytes of the message body when the message is in read-only mode. The value returned can be used to allocate a byte array. The value returned is the entire length of the message body, regardless of where the pointer for reading the message is currently located.
        Returns:
        number of bytes in the message
        Throws:
        AnyRuntimeException - Any exception that occurs in the underlying JMS provider implementation is thrown as a AnyRuntimeException

      • read

        Any read(Any type)
        Read a value from the bytes message stream according to the type of the given argument.
        Parameters:
        type - a value to characterise the type of read performed on the underlying bytes message. The argument is assigned to and returned.
        Returns:
        the value read - the type argument is returned.
        Throws:
        AnyRuntimeException - Any exception that occurs in the underlying JMS provider implementation is thrown as a AnyRuntimeException
